narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend SOCY 237 to another student if and only if Elizabeth Roberto isn't involved. I felt I learned a lot, and will be able to use these skills going forward.
If you're interested in agent-based modeling and programming, check this class out. Be prepared to do a lot of readings and to learn a coding language in some depth.
Interesting topic, but prepare for a lot of work for the final project!

no. esp if you're a sociology major, you will have no idea what's going on. learning "R" to do the final project is basically an entirely self-driven project that will take you forever if you don't already know it.assignments are not well-thought out, and you are just thrown into a course where you have to create a detailed, sophisticated computer generated model without any real practice. the assignments are not detailed and were not written in ways that would really prepare students to do the project, or to learn R.
I wouldn't recommend this course. It was pretty boring and didn't teach much. It was definitely a mistake to have a mixed class of sociology people and computer people.
